{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"24c64a03-af38-4c4a-8611-c8ee1a6eac84","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_tPNkRRv2LN8nbVCLM3cte6","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-db9429113b2140c99175c37a41a21787/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-db9429113b2140c99175c37a41a21787/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"bf04c698-6d65-43f9-a14c-413ad31c626c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear earlier in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), and `Program.fs` depends on both. So the correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` first (no dependencies)\n2. `Services.fs` second (depends on Domain)\n\n\n3. `Program.fs` third (depends on both)\n\nI need to reorder these files in the `.fsproj` to fix the compilation error.","outputTokens":476,"requestId":"2826:5FB6B:1C00AA4:1F0E8C6:69FA8FE9"},"id":"edb89b8a-fdbe-4205-915b-9a4f97d23d9c","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:48:50.191Z","parentId":"6aacdb06-674f-47f9-b90b-238932c27e2f"}
